# Domain Model

## Three core types
- `TestingModel` — engineer's calibration data. Shared across projects via JSON file.
  Contains: CalibrationEntry[], BrowserCalibrationEntry[], OverheadFactors,
  DeliverableEstimate[], ExploratoryBlock[].
- `ProjectSpec` — one client project's intake answers. One JSON file per project.
- `ScheduleOutput` — computed from Model + Project. Never persisted. Always recomputed.

## The calculation formula
  CellEstimate = BaseEstimate(testType, complexity) at Standard rigor
               × RIGOR_MULTIPLIERS[rigorLevel]      (Smoke=0.5, Standard=1.0, Enhanced=1.5, Audit=2.2)
               × BROWSER_SCALING[browserTier]       (CrossBrowser and Responsive only)

  RetestingEstimate  = ExecutionSubtotal × DEFECT_DENSITY_MULTIPLIERS[density]
  RegressionEstimate = RetestingEstimate × 0.60
  CoordOverhead      = ExecutionSubtotal × coordinationFraction
  ReportOverhead     = ExecutionSubtotal × reportingFraction
  GrandTotal         = sum of all the above + deliverables

## Certainty levels
- High   — exact (testType, complexity) base-rate entry found
- Medium — adjacent complexity entry found and interpolated
- Low    — no calibration data; cell is zero; flagged for engineer review

## Conditional test types
`deriveActiveTestTypes()` in projectHelpers.ts determines which test types are active.
Always call it — never set `selectedTestTypes` manually. It runs automatically inside
`updateDraft()` in IntakeView whenever any intake field changes.

## CalibrationEntry.pageCategory is optional
When undefined, the entry is a base rate (applies to all page categories).
The engine checks for exact (pageCategory, testType, complexity) matches first,
then falls back to base rates, degrading certainty accordingly.

## E2E automation is a summary line item
TestType.E2EAutomation is filtered out of the matrix columns.
It appears in deliverableLineItems in the summary section instead.
